.TH "pcie_pme_mark_devices" 9 "pcie_pme_mark_devices" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcie_pme_mark_devices \- Set the wakeup flag for devices below a port.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pcie_pme_mark_devices
.BI "(struct pci_dev *port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
PCIe root port or event collector to handle.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For each device below given root port, including the port itself (or for each
root complex integrated endpoint if \fIport\fP is a root complex event collector)
set the flag indicating that it can signal run-time wake-up events.
